1 (c) The following sections of Title 4, Subtitle 2 (“Issuance or Denial of Local
2 Licenses”) of Division I of this article apply in the county:
3 (5) § 4–208 (“Notice of license application required”), subject to [§] §§
4 26–1511 AND 26–1512 of this subtitle;
5 26–1511.
6 (c) (1) Before holding a hearing, the Board shall publish a notice of the hearing
7 [in at least two newspapers of general circulation in the county.
8 (2) The notice shall be published] ON THE BOARD’S WEBSITE, THROUGH
9 SOCIAL MEDIA, AND BY E–MAIL at least 30 days before the date by which license
10 applications are required to be filed for consideration at the hearing.
11 [(3)] (2) The notice shall contain:
12 (i) the number of licenses of each class that are available for
13 issuance;
14 (ii) a description of each class;
15 (iii) the date by which license applications must be filed to be
16 considered at the license application hearing; and
17 (iv) the date of the hearing.
18 26–1512.
19 (a) In addition to the [newspaper] INTERNET, SOCIAL MEDIA, AND E–MAIL
20 notice required under [§ 4–208 of this article] § 26–1511 OF THIS SUBTITLE, the Board
21 shall post a suitable notice in a conspicuous place at the location described in an application
22 for at least 10 days before the application hearing.
23 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect July
24 1, 2026.

